This paper deals with image deraining using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes novel loss functions and network structures, which involves training the network using intrinsic priors and multi-scale features, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of group convolution and feature sharing to improve network efficiency, which falls under the graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
